<P>
14 HAITIANS DIE IN ATTACK WITH TRUCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A suspected paramilitary group member drove a truck into a pro-democracy 
demonstration in a town west of the Haitian capital Sunday, killing at least 14 
people. 
</P>
<P>
 Journalists at the scene in the town of Miragoane said witnesses identified 
the driver as a member of the Front for the Advancement and Progress of Haiti 
(FRAPH), the country's most feared paramilitary group. The witnesses said he 
deliberately drove his vehicle into the rally and sped away. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the second incident in three days involving a vehicle plowing into 
supporters of exiled President Jean-Bertrand Aristide. On Friday, a bus drove 
into a demonstration in St.-Marc, killing at least four people. 
