<HEADLINE>
<P>
UNIVERSITY HOMECOMING QUEEN, 48, IS CROWNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mona Cohn, a 48-year-old honors student majoring in justice administration, 
was crowned University of Louisville homecoming queen Saturday, beating out 
women young enough to be her daughters. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is the best the thing that happened to me since my son 28 years ago," 
Cohn said. "I hope I've made a statement for the non-traditional student." 
</P>
