<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; PUBLIC GETS A CRACK AT GRILLING 
CANDIDATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The League of Women Voters, Huntington Beach Unit, is seeking questions from 
the public to ask City Council candidates at a forum Oct. 20. 
</P>
<P>
 Candidates have been invited to appear at the 5:30 to 9:30 p.m. forum at the 
City Council Chambers, 2000 Main St. Twenty-three candidates are vying for four 
seats on the council. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum, co-sponsored by the Huntington Beach Chapters of the American Assn. 
of University Women and the League of Women Voters, is an opportunity for the 
public to hear the candidates talk about local issues. 
</P>
<P>
 Questions may be mailed to: Rita Healy, League of Women Voters, P.O. Box 2120, 
Huntington Beach 92647. More information: (714) 840-7317. 
</P>
<P>
 The league's election guide, which provides voter information on candidates at 
the county, state and federal level and an analysis of county and state ballot 
issues, will be available at the forum and at city libraries. DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
