<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: LATINO GROUP TAKING NOMINATIONS FOR LEADERSHIP AWARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRED ALVAREZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 El Concilio del Condado de Ventura is accepting nominations for its 6th Annual 
Latino Leadership Awards.Nominations are due by 5 p.m. Oct. 19. 
</P>
<P>
 Awards are given to those who have made outstanding contributions to Ventura 
County's Latino community in business, arts, education, community service and 
youth. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, Oxnard School District trustee Mary Barreto and Rodney Fernandez, 
an advocate for affordable housing, were among the recipients. 
</P>
<P>
 Awards will be presented at a banquet Jan. 27. 
</P>
<P>
 El Concilio is an Oxnard-based nonprofit Latino advocacy organization serving 
the entire county. To nominate someone or for more information, call El 
Concilio at 983-2336. FRED ALVAREZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
