WOMAN'S DEATH, SHOOTING PROBED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles police on Sunday were investigating the death of a woman whose 
body was found in the debris of a burned Van Nuys house as well as a shooting 
that left one person dead and another wounded. 
</P>
<P>
 The body of the 77-year-old woman was discovered after firefighters put out a 
4:11 p.m. fire in the 6400 block of Blewett Avenue, Los Angeles Fire Department 
spokesman Jim Wells said. 
</P>
<P>
 At 4:45 p.m., one person was killed and another wounded in a shooting near Van 
Nuys Boulevard and Riverside Drive in Van Nuys, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
