<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN WANTED IN 3 SLAYINGS IS ARRESTED WITH $61,500 IN CASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man sought by Arkansas authorities in connection with three slayings was 
arrested along with his cousin in Altadena after Los Angeles County sheriff's 
deputies found them with two plastic grocery bags filled with $61,500 in cash. 
</P>
<P>
 Joe Kelley, 31, and Anthony Kelley, 30, were taken into custody Friday and 
booked for investigation of robbery after they could not explain to deputies 
how they got the money, Deputy Irma Becerra said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 During booking, deputies learned that Joe Kelley was wanted in Little Rock in 
connection with the shooting deaths of three men. He was being held Sunday 
pending extradition proceedings. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies also discovered that Anthony Kelley was wanted on a Pasadena 
narcotics violation. He was being held Sunday in lieu of $35,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
 The men were arrested outside an apartment complex in the 600 block of 
Altadena Drive after deputies, who were on a routine investigation, saw them 
sitting in a car in the parking lot. Police spotted the bags filled with $100 
and $50 bills in their vehicle, Becerra said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
