<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; MAN, 32, ARRESTED AFTER TRUCK FLIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 32-year-old Palmdale man was arrested on suspicion of felony drunk driving 
Sunday after his pickup truck flipped over, ejecting two children from the 
truck's bed, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Christopher Beliousky was speeding on Avenue P, west of 30th Street West about 
4:40 a.m. when he lost control of his Chevy S-10 pickup truck, the Los Angeles 
County Sheriff's Department reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Beliousky, after driving off the side of the road, tried to steer the truck 
back onto the freeway, causing it to flip over, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two children, ages 7 and 9, were ejected from the bed of the truck, 
authorities said. Beliousky's wife and a 2-year-old child were riding with him 
in the cab of the truck, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 All five people were taken to the Antelope Valley Hospital Medical Center, 
where they were treated for minor injuries and released, a hospital spokeswoman 
said. 
</P>
