PEOPLE: SANTA ANA-BASED WICOR SUBSIDIARY GETS NEW PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 J. Russell Phillips has been named president and chief executive of SHURflo 
Pump Manufacturing Co.Phillips, 45, succeeds John W. Casey Jr. who continues on 
the company's board. Prior to joining the Santa Ana-based subsidiary of Wicor 
Inc., Phillips was general manager of Goulds Pumps in the City of Industry. 
Wicor, which is based in Milwaukee, acquired SHURflo in 1993. 
