<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: FOUNTAIN VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ordinance Adopted to Set Direction for Sidewalk Cyclists 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council has adopted an ordinance that requires bicyclists riding on 
the sidewalk to travel in the same direction as traffic on the adjacent street. 
</P>
<P>
 The ordinance, which received final approval last week, applies to sidewalks 
along major streets, not those along residential streets. 
</P>
<P>
 Violation of the ordinance will be punishable by a fine of $25 for the first 
offense, said police Sgt. Larry Griswold. 
</P>
<P>
 The ordinance is expected to result in fewer accidents between bicycles and 
vehicles when the bicycles cross perpendicular streets and driveways, Griswold 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Griswold said that in 1991, there were 14 injury accidents involving bicycles. 
In 1992, that number rose to 36, and last year to 42. 
</P>
<P>
 Police plan to start enforcing the ordinance the first week of November, 
Griswold said. DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
