<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: TUSTIN; CHALLENGER QUITS SCHOOL BOARD RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Karen M. Judkin has withdrawn as a school board candidate for the Tustin 
Unified School District in the Nov. 8 election. 
</P>
<P>
 Judkin, a business consultant, said last week that she withdrew because her 
family is moving out of the school district.She was running for a four-year 
seat on the board. 
</P>
<P>
 Her name will appear in the ballot, she said, because it was too late to have 
it removed, but she has told supporters that she has stopped campaigning. 
</P>
<P>
 With her withdrawal, six candidates will vie for the two open seats, including 
incumbents Jane Bauer, Nancy Cast and Gloria Matta Tuchman. The other 
candidates are businessmen Jonathan W. Abelove and Nimesh Desai, and Robert L. 
Douglas, a maintenance services employee. 
</P>
<P>
 Five other candidates are seeking a two-year seat on the board: Gail 
Michelsen, a computer product manager; Robert D. Machado, a computer software 
engineer; Jon H. Soeder, a business owner; David A. Lampert, a business owner, 
and Malcolm D. Jones, a part-time professor at UC Irvine. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
