<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; FIREFIGHTERS PROMOTE SAFETY AND PREVENTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In observation of national Fire Prevention Week, which began Sunday, open 
houses will be held at all Orange County Fire Department stations from 9 a.m. 
to 4 p.m. next Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The theme of Fire Prevention Week is "Test Your Detector for Life!" Fire 
officials are encouraging residents to check their smoke detectors monthly and 
replace the batteries annually. 
</P>
<P>
 Events are planned at the following locations: 
</P>
<P>
 * Station 11, 259 Emerald Drive, Emerald Bay: ropes and rigging demonstration, 
ladder demonstration and simulated rescue using the "Jaws of Life." 
</P>
<P>
 * Station 54, 19811 Pauling Ave., Foothill Ranch: display of paramedic and 
firefighting equipment, and "Plan to Get Out Alive" video presentation. 
</P>
<P>
 * Station 4, 2 California Ave., Irvine: hazardous materials equipment display. 
</P>
<P>
 * Station 26, 4691 Walnut Ave., Irvine: simulated structure fire and medical 
aid responses, vehicle fire and aerial ladder demonstrations, and "Jaws of 
Life" demonstration. 
</P>
<P>
 * Station 5, 23600 Pacific Island Drive, Laguna Niguel: heart monitor 
demonstration, video on 1993 firestorm, fire engine demonstration, Smokey Bear 
video presentation. 
</P>
<P>
 * Station 39, 24241 Avila Road, Laguna Niguel: races for children and water 
squirt contest. 
</P>
<P>
 * Station 49, 31461 Street of the Golden Lantern, Laguna Niguel: rescue 
helicopter display, demonstrations of vehicle fire, rappelling and "Jaws of 
Life." 
</P>
<P>
 * Station 16, 28891 Modjeska Canyon Road, Modjeska: cardiopulmonary 
resuscitation and first aid demonstration, community barbecue and games. 
</P>
<P>
 * Station 45, 30131 Aventura, Rancho Santa Margarita: simulated structure fire 
response, aerial rescue demonstration, smoke detector testing. 
</P>
<P>
 * Station 7, 31865 Del Obispo, San Juan Capistrano: demonstrations of 
automatic defibrillator, "Jaws of Life" and vehicle fire, and races for 
children. 
</P>
<P>
 * Station 21, 1241 Irvine Blvd., Tustin: "Jaws of Life" demonstration and 
aerial equipment display.ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
