<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: LAGUNA NIGUEL; NEW SPEED LIMITS TO BE ADOPTED ON 3 ROADS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has voted to increase the speed limit on one street and 
establish two new speed limits in the city. 
</P>
<P>
 City staff recommended the changes to comply with a state law that requires 
enforceable speed limits be posted. 
</P>
<P>
 The speed limit on La Paz Road between Crown Valley Parkway and Rancho Niguel 
Road will increase from 40 to 45 m.p.h. A traffic survey found that the average 
speed there is 48 m.p.h. 
</P>
<P>
 The new speed limits will be on Talavera Drive and a section of the newly 
extended Cabot Road. Cars will not be allowed to travel more than 30 m.p.h. on 
Talavera, or more than 45 m.p.h. on Cabot Road between Crown Valley Parkway and 
the city's northern boundary. 
</P>
<P>
 The traffic survey showed that the average speed on Cabot Road between Rapid 
Falls Road and the city limits is also 48 m.p.h. LYNN FRANEY 
