<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTHER, 2 CHILDREN INJURED FLEEING FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A mother and two daughters were injured Sunday morning as they escaped a fire 
in their two-story townhouse, fire officials reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Tam Dang, 26, was awakened shortly after 7 a.m. on the second floor of the 
condominium at 13934 Parkway Drive by her 2-year-old daughter, Dina Nguyen. 
Fire had broken out in the first-floor living room, according to a Garden Grove 
Fire Department news release. 
</P>
<P>
 Dang was unable to take Dina and her 4-year-old daughter, Gina Nguyen, down 
the stairs because of fire and smoke. 
</P>
<P>
 She ended up dropping the girls through the second-floor window into the arms 
of downstairs tenants who had been awakened by the family's shouting. The 
mother then jumped from the window, injuring her ankle. 
</P>
