<HEADLINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON BEACH WOMAN, 81, KILLED IN CRASH; 2 HURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 81-year-old Huntington Beach woman was killed late Saturday night and two 
other people were seriously injured when two cars collided at a local 
intersection, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ann Goldfein was pronounced dead at UCI Medical Center, a spokesman for the 
Orange County coroner's office said. 
</P>
<P>
 Goldfein was riding in a 1982 Mercedes Benz driven by Martha Baumel, 52, of 
Huntington Beach when it collided with a 1975 Chevy truck driven by David 
Zunig, 20, of Costa Mesa, said Lt. Jim Cutshaw of the Huntington Beach Police 
Department. Baumel and Zunig were hospitalized with major head and internal 
injuries, Cutshaw said. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses said the Mercedes Benz was "going at a high rate of speed" westbound 
on Bolsa Avenue at 11:50 p.m. when it entered the Springdale Street 
intersection and collided with the truck, Cutshaw said. The collision knocked 
both cars into a nearby field, Cutshaw said. 
</P>
<P>
 Zunig was taken to Huntington Beach Medical Center. His condition Sunday was 
not released. 
</P>
<P>
 Baumel's condition also was not released Sunday night at UCI Medical Center. 
</P>
