<P>
 Regional Business Outlook Conference: A panel discussion about incentives to 
create and retain business and the effect of government regulation on the 
business community will be featured at the 46th annual Los Angeles Area Chamber 
of Commerce business outlook conference, which will be held Tuesday at the 
Biltmore Hotel in Downtown Los Angeles. Southern California has become a 
favored hunting ground for out-of-towners looking to lure away companies 
unhappy with the area's business climate, although statistics indicate that the 
exodus slowed this year. Conference speakers will include state Assembly 
Speaker Willie L. Brown, RLA Chief Executive Linda Griego, AirTouch 
Communications Chief Executive Sam Ginn and businessman and former Dallas 
Cowboys quarterback Roger Staubach. 
</P>
