<P>
 Export Outreach Center: The Export Small Business Development Center will open 
an outreach center in El Monte on Thursday to help San Gabriel Valley 
businesses interested in foreign trade become better at building export 
markets. The Export SBDC was formed three years ago to help small businesses 
throughout Southern California increase exports.The program is a partnership 
involving the Small Business Administration, the California Trade and Commerce 
Agency and the Export Managers Assn. of California. The El Monte outreach 
center is designed to provide assistance in expanding export markets by 
offering consulting services to businesses and access to trade and export 
information. The center also plans to hold regular seminars and workshops on 
trade and export issues. Export SBDC officials said El Monte was chosen for an 
outreach center because of the strong manufacturing base in the San Gabriel 
Valley. Forty percent of the businesses in the valley are involved in 
manufacturing. The outreach center will open at 10501 Valley Blvd. Export SBDC 
officials say the program, which also has offices in Los Angeles, Long Beach 
and Oxnard, helped clients export $115 million in products last year. The 
increase helped create 2,000 jobs for the local economy, they say. An open 
house, hosted by the El Monte/South El Monte Chamber of Commerce, will be held 
at the center from 2 to 7 p.m. 
</P>
